# Design: Admin Dashboard Final Polish

## Technical Approach

Complete admin UI by adding nested `/admin/*` workflows and a shared operational shell, while shifting route authority from `sessionStorage` to backend-verifiable access probes against existing `/api/admin/**` endpoints. Catalog job operations will be closed by making cancel explicitly non-actionable in UI until backend cancel semantics are implemented, and by exposing row/report diagnostics already available in current APIs.

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Options | Tradeoff | Choice |
|---|---|---|---|
| Admin auth authority | A) Keep `sessionStorage` gate B) Bootstrap guard from backend probe | A is fast but false-positive/false-negative on refresh; B adds one request but aligns with security truth | **B** — guard resolves `loading/authenticated/unauthenticated/forbidden` from backend response (401 vs 403) |
| Admin route structure | A) Single `/admin` page with local tabs B) Nested routes under `/admin` | A simpler initial file count; B better deep-linking and testability | **B** — add child routes for products/categories/orders/jobs |
| Catalog cancel closure | A) Wire cancel button to current endpoint B) Hide/disable cancel until contract is real | A exposes known `501 NOT_IMPLEMENTED`; B avoids broken action | **B** — non-actionable cancel with explanatory status text |
| Typing strategy | A) `Record<string, unknown>` B) typed DTOs mirroring backend | A quicker but runtime drift risk; B more upfront types | **B** — strict interfaces for touched responses and requests |

## Data Flow

```text
Admin URL (/admin/*)
   -> AdminGuard
      -> adminAccess.bootstrapAdminSession() [GET /api/admin/orders?size=1]
         -> 2xx: allow + render AdminShell/child page
         -> 401: show login-entry UX
         -> 403: show forbidden UX

Admin workflow page
   -> adminOperationsService typed call
      -> backend /api/admin/{products|categories|orders|catalog/jobs}
         -> render list/detail/empty states

Catalog job details
   -> GET /api/admin/catalog/jobs/{id}
   -> GET /api/admin/catalog/jobs/{id}/rows
   -> GET /api/admin/catalog/jobs/{id}/report
      -> display status + row/report errors; cancel displayed disabled
```

