## Interfaces / Contracts

```ts
type AdminAccessState = 'loading' | 'authenticated' | 'unauthenticated' | 'forbidden'

interface AdminOrderListResponse {
  items: Array<{
    id: string
    reference: string
    status: string
    customer: string
    total: string
    createdAt: string
  }>
  page: number
  size: number
  totalElements: number
  totalPages: number
}

interface AdminCatalogJobResponse {
  id: string
  jobType: string
  status: 'QUEUED' | 'PROCESSING' | 'COMPLETED' | 'FAILED'
  summary: string | null
  lastError: string | null
}
```

Cancel contract in this change: UI MUST treat `POST /api/admin/catalog/jobs/{id}/cancel` as unsupported and never expose it as active action.

## Testing Strategy

| Layer | What to Test | Approach |
|---|---|---|
| Unit | `adminAccess` state mapping from 2xx/401/403 and logout clearing | Vitest with mocked `fetch`/`ApiClientError` |
| Integration | Guard + route behavior for refresh/direct URL and role outcomes | RTL + `MemoryRouter` covering `/admin/*` transitions |
| Integration | Admin service DTO alignment (orders `items`, job rows/report) | Service tests with response fixtures matching backend records |
| E2E-lite | Admin shell workflow navigation and empty states | Existing frontend test stack route-render assertions |

## Migration / Rollout

No migration required. Rollout is a frontend patch behind existing `adminDashboardEnabled` flag and current backend endpoints.

